menu.commands

Class PrintCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • menu.commands.PrintCommand
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Command

    public class PrintCommand
extends java.lang.Object
implements Command
    The PrintCommand class implements the Command interface to print the contents of the table to the console.

    If any cell in the table contains a formula, it is calculated using the Formula1 class. The updated contents of the table are then printed. 

     
 Table table = new Table(new TypeChecker());
 Printer printer = new Printer(table);
 Formula1 formula1 = new Formula1(table);
 PrintCommand printCommand = new PrintCommand(printer, formula1);
 printCommand.execute(new String[] {"print"});

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        public void execute(java.lang.String[] data)
             throws ClosedFileException
        Executes the print command. This method performs the following steps:
        1. Checks if the table's file is open.
        2. If the file is open, any formulas in the cells are calculated using the formula evaluator.
        3. The contents of the table are then printed to the console.
        4. If an unexpected error occurs, an appropriate error message is displayed.
        Specified by:
        execute in interface Command
        Parameters:
        data - an array of command parts
        Throws:
        ClosedFileException - if the table's file is closed
